I think this behavior could be useful when you are using AABBs for collision detection, to set the position of particles for example 

Here's a possible implentation. Maybe should avoid creating a new one and instead cache it, or have an extra "out" parameter 

```
public static Rectangle intersection(Rectangle r1, Rectangle r2) {
    float r1x1 = r1.x, r1x2 = r1.x + r1.width;
    float r1y1 = r1.y, r1y2 = r1.y + r1.height;
    float r2x1 = r2.x, r2x2 = r2.x + r2.width;
    float r2y1 = r2.y, r2y2 = r2.y + r2.height;

    if (r1x1 < r2x1)
        r1x1 = r2x1;
    if (r1x2 > r2x2)
        r1x2 = r2x2;

    if (r1y1 < r2y1)
        r1y1 = r2y1;
    if (r1y2 > r2y2)
        r1y2 = r2y2;


    return new Rectangle(r1x1, r1y1, r1x2 - r1x1, r1y2 - r1y1);
}
```

