I ran into this problem while using a Label with a Drawable background:
All elements drawn by the same batch object, in my case the stage's batch, fade in and out because of an action which has been added to the Label.
In the draw Method of Label, the color of the used batch is set to use the alpha value calculated from the active action but never set back to normal:

```
public void draw (SpriteBatch batch, float parentAlpha) {
    validate();
    Color color = getColor();
    if (style.background != null) {
        batch.setColor(color.r, color.g, color.b, color.a * parentAlpha);
        style.background.draw(batch, getX(), getY(), getWidth(), getHeight());
    }
```

Is this the intended behaviour? I don't hope so because now I have to reset the color of the batch after every Label.draw() call.
